<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,862]" box="[199,587,510,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName authority="Seitz, 1909" authorityName="Seitz" authorityYear="1909" box="[199,587,510,537]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="changaica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,451,510,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">M. phoebe changaica</emphasis>
Seitz, 1909
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,862]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry box="[656,768,511,537]" name="Mongolia" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, Changai (Khangai or Hangayn) Mountains] uppersides of a male and female were figured by Seitz (plate 65, figs h 4 &amp; 5).However, www.funet.fi (accessed 
<date box="[1301,1429,547,574]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="2020-10-26">26.10.2020</date>
) provides a photograph (© Kosterin) of undersides of a male and female of this this subspecies in 
<emphasis box="[1295,1371,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">copula</emphasis>
from Chikhalan, Chita Province, S. Transbaikalia, Siberia, 
<collectingCountry box="[756,972,619,645]" name="Russia" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
(
<date box="[989,1140,619,646]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="1996-07-12">12 July 1996</date>
); from the photograph the characteristics typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[438,559,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[438,559,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be observed, in particular the black submarginal markings clearly touch the intervening veins on both wings of the 
<specimenCount box="[629,797,691,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
. Also figured (© Kosterin) is a post-diapause larvae, also from the Chita region in Siberia (
<date box="[522,674,726,753]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" value="1995-06-19">19 June 1995</date>
), with a black head carapace typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1232,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[1114,1232,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A specimen from Changai in the Staudinger collection (
<figureCitation box="[582,664,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1868,1892]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,885,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-371@5.[151,1436,885,1845]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 12. Melitaea phoebe changaica Seitz, 1909, male underside. © T. Léger." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577642/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) clearly shows the club-shaped antennae and submarginal markings on the underside typical of 
<taxonomicName box="[455,573,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[455,573,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This taxon is therefore considered to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1326,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[1208,1326,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, agreeing with 
<bibRefCitation author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[208,602,835,862]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 60)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[657,981,834,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016: 45</bibRefCitation>
, note 24).
</paragraph>
